00001 //======= Copyright (c) Valve Corporation, All rights reserved. ===============
00002 // Action implementation overview:
00003 // Actions are split into three parts:
00004 //     * Action: The user-accessible class that is the interface for accessing action data. 
00005 //          There may be many Action instances per Actual SteamVR Action, but these instances are just interfaces to the data and should have virtually no overhead.
00006 //     * Action Map: This is basically a wrapper for a list of Action_Source instances. 
00007 //          The idea being there is one Map per Actual SteamVR Action. 
00008 //          These maps can be retrieved from a static store in SteamVR_Input so we're not duplicating data.
00009 //     * Action Source: This is a collection of cached data retrieved by calls to the underlying SteamVR Input system. 
00010 //          Each Action Source has an inputSource that it is associated with.
00011 
